            <tbody>
               <tr>
                  <td style="padding:0; width:5%;" width="5%">&nbsp;</td>
                  <td class="fallback-font" style="padding: 0; font-weight:normal; font-family: Arial, arial;line-height:22.4px;font-size:14px;color:#363636"><p><span style="font-size: 13pt;"><strong>Considering taking a Summer Course and transferring it back to UIC? &nbsp;</strong></span><br />Students interested in picking up courses at a different institution during the summer are required to obtain a parent letter from UIC to grant the secondary institution permission to use GI benefits. Courses must be required to satisfy the degree that is pursued at the parent institution. This is especially important for any student who plans to take classes concurrently at the parent and secondary institution. To begin this appeal process, visit the Benefits and forms tab on the Student Veterans Affairs <a style="color: #d50032;" title="SVA Benefits and Forms website link" href="https://dos.uic.edu/student-veterans-affairs/benefits-and-forms" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="color: #d50032; font-weight: bold;">webpage</span></a> and select the Benefit Appeal Form. Once the appeal is received and reviewed, students will receive guidance on the next steps, which includes working with their advisors to complete a transfer credit verification form to confirm how courses will apply to a UIC degree.</p></td>
                  <td style="padding:0; width:5%;" width="5%">&nbsp;</td>
